    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/org/866ab3d86d49",
      "@type": "schema:Organization",
      "schema:name": "Rf-Technologies",
      "schema:address": null,
      "schema:addressCountry": null
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/person/dbb5748d05f5",
      "@type": "schema:Person",
      "schema:name": "Bob Roijen",
      "verificationType": "independent_third_party"
    },
    {
      "@id": "http://localhost:3000/id/epd/http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A3000%2Fid%2Fepd%2FB-EPD%2520024.0263.001-01.00.00%2520Fire%2520damper%2520RF-Technologies-EN_signed/product",
      "@type": "ProductSection",
      "description": "CU-LT 200x100 is an optimised rectangular fire damper with a fire resistance up to 120 minutes. It is the smallest type of a fire damper series and has a width of 200 mm and a height of 100 mm. A minimal pressure loss is guaranteed thanks to the thin blade and the transmission located outside the tunnel. A galvanised steel tunnel contributes to the light weight of the damper. The fire damper can be equipped with various types of mechanisms (motorised or not), depending on the specific needs linked to the project or to the local regulations. In this EPD, one specific motorised actuator is considered as a reference.\n\nFire dampers are installed where air ducts penetrate fire-resistant compartment walls. Their role is to restore the fire resistance grade of the penetrated wall and to prevent smoke propagation. Fire dampers are distinguished by their degree of fire resistance, by their aeraulic properties and by their installation ease. Rf-Technologies solutions are designed and approved for all types of walls: vertical and horizontal, in concrete or lightweight materials. They are compliant with the most stringent local and European standards. Furthermore, the products for the compartmentation and smoke control provide fire safety for commercial and institutional buildings across Europe: office buildings, hospitals, museums, multi-family housing, public buildings and shopping centres.\n\nIn general, a CU-LT fire damper consists of three main parts, i.e. a fire damper casing, mainly composed of a galvanised steel duct, a fire damper blade, composed of a 25 mm thick Promatect H plate, and an actuator (motorised or not). In this EPD, a motorised actuator is considered as a reference.\n\nThis EPD is a specific EPD for one specific product, i.e. CU-LT 200x100 fire damper with motorised actuator, from one single company, i.e. Rf-Technologies, that is produced in one single site, i.e. Oosterzele, Belgium.",
      "intendedUse": "Fire dampers are installed where air ducts penetrate fire-resistant compartment walls. Their role is to restore the fire resistance grade of the penetrated wall and to prevent smoke propagation. Fire dampers are distinguished by their degree of fire resistance, by their aeraulic properties and by their installation ease. Rf-Technologies solutions are designed and approved for all types of walls: vertical and horizontal, in concrete or lightweight materials. They are compliant with the most stringent local and European standards. Furthermore, the products for the compartmentation and smoke control provide fire safety for commercial and institutional buildings across Europe: office buildings, hospitals, museums, multi-family housing, public buildings and shopping centres.",
      "installation": "The product can be installed in different varieties, in respect with the Declaration of Performance (DoP):\n• Installation in a rigid wall and floor;\n• Installation in flexible wall (metal stud gypsum plasterboard wall);\n• Installation in flexible wall (metal stud gypsum plasterboard wall), sealing with gypsum;\n• Installation in flexible wall (metal stud gypsum plasterboard wall), sealing with mortar;\n• Installation in shaft wall, sealing with gypsum;\n• Installation in shaft wall, sealing with rigid rock wool boards with coating;\n• Installation in shaft wall with IFW installation kit and plaster joint filler;\n• Installation in flexible and rigid wall, sealing with rigid rock wool boards with coating;\n• Installation in rigid floor, sealing with rigid rock wool boards with coating;\n• Installation remote from the wall, sealing and insulation with rigid rock wool boards with coating;\n• Installation remote from the wall + GEOFLAM plates (threaded rods and U-shaped steel profiles).\n\nBecause of the different ways of installation, the product is declared as 'as produced'' in this EPD.\n\nConsequently, regarding installation, this EPD only includes the environmental impact related to the product itself (i.e. treatment of the waste arising from the packaging of the final product). The impact of possible additional products and materials, necessary for the installation of the product, is not included in this EPD. However, this impact shall be taken into account at building level.\n\nMore detailed information on the different installation scenarios can be found in the chapter \"Additional technical information for scenario development\" in this EPD.",
      "referenceServiceLifeYears": 30,
      "geographicalRepresentativity": "The CU-LT 200x100 fire damper with motorised actuator is produced in Belgium by the Belgian company Rf-Technologies and is installed in Belgium. The EPD is representative for the Belgian market. The composed datasets for this EPD are representative and relevant for a CU-LT 200x100 fire damper with motorised actuator produced by Rf-Technologies in Belgium.",
      "productionProcess": "For the production of the CU-LT 200x100 fire damper, at first, the parts for the calcium silicate damper blade and the metal tunnel body are produced as sub-assembly parts. These two parts come together in the final assembly line. Here, the following steps are performed: assembly of the damper blade, assembly of the transmission, mounting of the actuator on the damper, adding labels, end control and test. Finally, the finished and tested fire damper is packed.",
      "referenceFlow": {
        "@type": "schema:QuantitativeValue",
        "schema:value": 1,
        "schema:unitCode": "piece",
        "description": "The functional unit for this EPD is 1 CU-LT 200x100 fire damper with a motorised actuator, to be used in conjunction with partitions to maintain fire compartments in heating, ventilation and air conditioning installations, with a fire resistance up to 120 minutes and a reference service life of 30 years. Packaging of the raw materials and the finished product is included. The net weight per reference flow is 4,856 kg."
      }
    },
